summary: It hurts my heart because early on Caleb seemed to be sorta into Fjord. Like he saw Fjord as charismatic, a leader, he’d go to...
body:
It hurts my heart because early on Caleb seemed to be sorta into Fjord. Like he saw Fjord as charismatic, a leader, he’d go to Fjord and try to see what the best course of action was. 

He seemed to really be drawn to Fjord’s gentleness and heroics. I’ll never forget how Fjord asked Caleb earnestly about his fear of fire; and at the time Caleb was so into this guy that he admitted that he “…Used to hurt people….and that to please just ask me again in a few days and I’ll have a better answer for you. I don’t feel safe yet with these people I don’t trust everyone to not turn on me yet not even Nott.” 

Aaaaaand then the scroll thing happened. And it’s not that Caleb was really mad at Fjord or held a grudge (he even says to Nott that he understands why they’re mad even if he personally disagrees. He even attempted to patch things up with Fjord first and Fjord sorta shot him down), it’s that the event proves to him that if Fjord found out what Caleb used to be, Fjord would judge him and turn on him.

summary: Title: map to alexandria Pairing: Caleb/Mollymauk Chapters: 1/[ongoing] Words: 5,555 Caleb gave up the piano years ago. When his...
body:
Title: map to alexandria
Pairing: Caleb/Mollymauk
Chapters: 1/[ongoing]
Words: 5,555

Caleb gave up the piano years ago. When his friend Fjord is getting married and he rejects his request to play at the wedding, it’s the least he can do to teach someone else how to play in his stead.

His “student,” Mollymauk, is more than some random tiefling with an ear for music, though; he’s the lead singer of rock band.

It’s more than just their tastes in music that clash when they’re forced to come together, and Caleb doesn’t see himself escaping the other unscathed.

Read on AO3 | Kofi
